<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-230] use of variable inside closure seems broken</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-230</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;reported by brianm - the value of &apos;sql&apos; appears to be considered a property of the builder first.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;#!/usr/bin/env groovy&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;import groovy.sql.Sql&lt;br/&gt;
import groovy.xml.MarkupBuilder&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;sql = Sql.newInstance(&quot;jdbc:postgresql://localhost/mydb?charSet=UTF-8&quot;, &lt;br/&gt;
                      &quot;foo&quot;, &quot;bar&quot;,&lt;br/&gt;
                      &quot;org.postgresql.Driver&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;doc = new MarkupBuilder()&lt;br/&gt;
doc.projects() {&lt;br/&gt;
    sql.eachRow(&quot;select * from profiles&quot;) &lt;/p&gt;
{
        doc.profile(first: it.firstname, last: it.lastname, email: it.email)
    }
&lt;p&gt;}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;sql.close()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;println doc&lt;/p&gt;</description>
